agreements datacube documentation

Source: R/manytrade-agreements.R
agreements.Rd

agreements datacube documentation

Usage

agreements

Format

The agreements datacube is a list that contains the following 7 datasets: DESTA, GPTAD, LABPTA, TOTA, TREND, HUGGO, AIGGO. For more information and references to each of the datasets used, please use the manydata::call_sources() and manydata::compare_dimensions() functions.

DESTA:

A dataset with 959 observations and the following 10 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, AgreementType, DocType, GeogArea, Signature, Force, destaID.

GPTAD:

A dataset with 340 observations and the following 10 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, AgreementType, DocType, GeogArea, Signature, Force, gptadID.

LABPTA:

A dataset with 483 observations and the following 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, labptaID.

TOTA:

A dataset with 442 observations and the following 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, totaID.

TREND:

A dataset with 710 observations and the following 7 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, trendID.

HUGGO:

A dataset with 610 observations and the following 11 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, End, url, Citation, TreatyText, Coder.

AIGGO:

A dataset with 1389 observations and the following 8 variables: manyID, treatyID, Title, Begin, Signature, Force, accessionC, accessionP.

Source

  • DESTA: A. Dür, L. Baccini, and M. Elsig. “The Design of International Trade Agreements: Introducing a NewDatabase”. In: The Review of International Organizations 9.3 (2014), pp. 353-375.

  • GPTAD: W. B. Group. Global Preferential Trade Agreement Database (GPTAD). Online database. publisher: WorldBank Group. 2014. https://wits.worldbank.org/gptad/library.aspx.

  • LABPTA: D. Raess, A. Dür, and D. Sari. “Protecting labor rights in preferential trade agreements: The role of trade unions, left governments, and skilled labor”. In: The Review of International Organizations 2.13(2018), pp. 143-162. DOI: 10.1007/s11558-018-9301-z.

  • TOTA: W. Alschner, J. Seiermann, and D. Skougarevskiy. Text-as-data analysis of preferential tradeagreements: Mapping the PTA landscape. 2017. https://github.com/mappingtreaties/tota.git.

  • TREND: J. Morin, A. Dür, and L. Lechner. “Mapping the trade and environment nexus: Insights from a newdataset”. In: Global Environmental Politics 18.1 (2018), pp. 122-139.

  • HUGGO: J. Hollway. Trade agreements for manydata. 2021.

  • AIGGO: J. Hollway. Trade agreements for manydata. 2021.

URL

  • DESTA: https://www.designoftradeagreements.org/downloads/

  • GPTAD: https://wits.worldbank.org/gptad/library.aspx

  • LABPTA: https://doi.org/10.1007/s11558-018-9301-z

  • TOTA: https://github.com/mappingtreaties/tota.git

  • TREND: http://www.chaire-epi.ulaval.ca/en/trend

  • HUGGO: Hand-coded data by the GGO team

  • AIGGO: Machine-generated data by the GGO team

Mapping

  • DESTA: Variable Mapping

    fromto
    base_treatydestaID
    nameTitle
    yearSignature
    entryforceyearForce
    typemembDocType
    entry_typeAgreementType
    regionconGeogArea

  • GPTAD: Variable Mapping

    fromto
    Common.NameTitle
    Date.of.SignatureSignature
    Date.of.Entry.into.ForceForce
    TypeDocType
    TypeAgreementType
    TypeGeogArea

  • LABPTA: Variable Mapping

    fromto
    NumberlabptaID
    NameTitle
    yearSignature
    yearForce

  • TOTA: Variable Mapping

    fromto
    nameTitle
    date_signedSignature
    date_into_forceForce

  • TREND: Variable Mapping

    fromto
    Trade.AgreementTitle
    YearSignature
    YearForce
